NFL Draft - Linear Regression Analysis¶

The purpose of this notebook is to perform multivariate linear regression analysis on the transformed position specific nfl draft data.

Analysis Functions¶

In [6]:
def create_corr_matrix(data, cols):
    return (pd.DataFrame(np.corrcoef(data[cols].T), index=cols, columns=cols)
            .style.background_gradient("coolwarm"))
In [7]:
def fit_summarize_lm(data, dep_col, ind_cols):
    y = data[dep_col].copy()
    X = data[ind_cols].copy()
    X = sm.add_constant(X)
    lm = sm.OLS(y, X)
    res = lm.fit()
    #print(res.summary())
    vifs = pd.Series({ind_cols[i]:variance_inflation_factor(data[ind_cols].values, i)
                      for i in range(len(ind_cols))})
    #print(vifs)
    return res, vifs
In [8]:
def write_outputs(lm_res, lm_vifs, position):
    with open("../analysis_outputs/{}_regression_summary.html".format(position), "w") as f:
        f.write(lm_res.summary().as_html())
    with open("../analysis_outputs/{}_regression_summary.txt".format(position), "w") as f:
        f.write(lm_res.summary().as_text())
    lm_vifs_df = lm_vifs.rename("VIF").reset_index().rename(columns={"index":"Variable"})
    lm_vifs_df.to_html("../analysis_outputs/{}_vifs.html".format(position), index=False)
    with open("../analysis_outputs/{}_vifs.txt".format(position), "w") as f:
        f.write(lm_vifs_df.to_string(index=False))
In [9]:
def plot_regresion_grid(lm):
    fig = plt.figure(figsize=(12,20))
    fig = sm.graphics.plot_partregress_grid(lm, fig=fig)
